Front view of a light khaki beige lace camisole. The garment features thin elastic fixed-length shoulder straps. The neckline is a V-shape with a scalloped lace edge that follows the neckline contour. The fabric is a single layer of soft, lightweight, and stretchable lace composed of a nylon and spandex blend with a matte finish. The surface displays an allover symmetrical floral pattern combined with a fine mesh background. The cups are softly contoured, and the lace pattern continues seamlessly across them. There is no horizontal seam under the bust; the lace pattern itself provides gentle shaping. The lower section of the camisole extends downward with a continuous floral lace design and finishes with a wide scalloped lace hem. The edges of the garment appear soft and naturally integrated with the lace pattern, creating a cohesive and elegant finish. Soft natural shadows and gentle folds are present along the garment contours, lace texture, and edges, contributing to a realistic and three-dimensional appearance. The garment is constructed as a single-piece pull-on style.
